[00:02.52]Forty days in the desert, dust on His skin
[00:04.99]Silence so loud, hear the war within
[00:06.72]Hunger in the body, Spirit standing tall
[00:08.90]Enemy whispers like he’s doing Him a favor, not a fall
[00:12.66]“If You’re really the Son, prove who You are
[00:16.17]Turn these stones to bread, show Your power, go far”
[00:19.61]But He stood on the Word, not the need of the flesh
[00:23.85]He didn’t bow to the moment, He trusted what’s next
[00:28.22]Every promise twisted, every lie dressed clean
[00:35.72]But truth don’t bend when temptation screams
[00:44.87]Stones don’t become bread when faith takes the stand
[00:59.64]Man don’t live by hunger but the Word in His hands
[01:17.61]From the peak to the pit, He never let go
[01:32.82]Kingdoms were offered, but He chose the cross road
[01:46.22]He said no to the crown, said yes to the will
[02:02.88]Victory whispered on a desert hill
[02:11.89]On the highest rooftop, wind in His face
[02:13.88]“Jump and the angels will catch You in grace”
[02:16.69]Scripture misquoted, truth turned thin
[02:18.18]But God’s Word ain’t a tool for the pride of men
[02:21.95]“You don’t test the Father, you trust His name”
[02:24.62]Not chasing spectacle, not playing games
[02:26.64]Strength in surrender, power restrained
[02:27.98]Heaven was watching, hell felt the pain
[02:30.15]Stones don’t become bread when faith takes the stand
[02:33.04]Man don’t live by hunger but the Word in His hands
[02:36.41]From the peak to the pit, He never let go
[02:39.18]Kingdoms were offered, but He chose the cross road
[02:41.84]He said no to the crown, said yes to the will
[02:44.77]Victory whispered on a desert hill
[02:46.64]Bow once, rule all, just worship me
[02:48.53]But the Lamb don’t kneel to the enemy
[02:51.06]Every knee gonna bow, every tongue confess
[02:53.02]But not by shortcuts, not by compromise stress
[02:55.59]Written Word sharp like a two-edged blade
[02:57.63]Devil left defeated when the Son obeyed
[02:59.78]Stones don’t become bread, lies don’t win
[03:02.29]Truth stood firm and the war caved in
[03:04.60]Tempted in all ways, yet without sin
[03:06.51]The battle was loud but the victory was Him
[03:09.34]Angels came running, strength restored
[03:11.10]The desert bloomed when He spoke the Word